                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Until very recently, treatment options were limited to topical creams and immunosuppressants, and not all patients respond similarly to the same treatment plan. But the landscape is changing. Today, researchers are uncovering the biological mechanisms behind the disease and developing treatments that help address the immune response.&lt;/p>&lt;p>As the scientific community continues to better understand the underlying genetics and internal processes involved in atopic dermatitis across individuals, the possibility for a more targeted approach to treatment comes into focus.&lt;/p>&lt;p>“We’re confident that the bar will soon be raised for the treatment of atopic dermatitis. The scientific community is on the cusp of bringing real change to help people live their lives more fully,” Dr. Pangan says.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_21>
